BRIEFLY 
Revco to Sell 712 Drugstores: Revco said it plans to sell 712 of its nearly 
1,900 drugstores in a bid to emerge from Chapter 11 bankruptcy proceedings. The 
privately held company, based in Twinsburg, Ohio, said it intends to sell 
stores in 17 Southeast and Midwest states and focus on its strongest operations 
of more than 1,100 drugstores in 10 Eastern states. 
